						'description' => 'Emily was born 23 weeks premature, so she was born with challenges. Everything was going well until Emily started running into things and her parents realized she was having trouble seeing. She has been blind in her right eye since birth, but has been able to see in her left. Emily’s opthamologist saw signs of inflammation in her eyes and was concerned that she was losing vision in her left eye. Emily was diagnosed with Uveitis. Since the diagnoses they have tried Rituximab, Remicade, and she is now getting Actemra. She gets her Actemra infusions every 8 weeks. Emily has most of her vision, but the medications have slowed the progression. Emily absolutely loves going in for her infusions at Shands!',
